y relative="1" as="geometry"><Array as="points"><mxPoint x="1507" y="1305"/><mxPoint x="1507" y="1351"/></Array></mxGeometry></mxCell><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   21k lives-eq/$1k · 70% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 30%&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v20YS%2FisD49qTUpkmqRdKyvkAJ5bboE4a2A6KIgqUFbmStiG57O7StC51f%2FvN7pISZdGwAH1JaHH2mWfedmb4%2FSSiC5LH6i2P6Mn45OwMzs%2FP4U4QloLiEAryvzU%2BFClMc9%2F1elBwEUf3jBZQeDN%2F1p8F0JKKZxC09dFpihAXUuZJphhPIVwh0hhcyIjg4YqRWAN5Ix88WBAxIwVZz1Z5QlJZvfCBpCwhsZxJntBiRVT1pg%2BLXOWClgdmCVGKilnB1GoWMRnyPFUsXVbiwQaoFCSzmCvDcELCFZAtTSaBwMe1WuHzgsUU0Pzta3kGStMgUSQ7ICj6jKVUAhcGTNBTtI4kFHUwib%2BrFbWG%2F1si4zQ0GK8h5EnGpSa4EcCzaUQREX9i0qBJRdKIxDylkGBQYge%2Bbnw%2Buf%2Bqqerj9CGjocKD9yTOKfCFQdiGxzFgb6hUMM%2FXkGs1%2BqCkdcPGcLsSLMngdxpjOCh8FPxPxLWnf558mNxc3E0uYb6GJU2pIIo62brKBRoxteOmV%2FiyAylXloz2JCIZrE9pSIXSJidcYBZsPCatrHUHybKYUenA7TpxYr5MucAAtr5n%2FQ5ko%2F5j22CZaI3cH%2BDtu9dGck4Vsb9mgs%2FJnMVMIZE512ZHOpE%2Fux3wvjhwRULFUSfaaqFQINMxSFUHJAeqE4OLJUZu8rm4vLj%2B4%2BxfX2BOY15gvuqzJsL0AZ%2FjNR5HbPSqwULdUR4qGwuMHsUcRfNtzl6W%2BQnn%2B7aNoUtP3aEx0T4PHtsAGhJPniqWUPgJQqKIVIJniK3zOc2JyV2dskScWjVlOrRuSCLp%2BuwWHZzCP%2