ls)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+7+8+9]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   66k lives-eq/$1k · 70% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 30%&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 9 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJytWG1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbO7tqKJL8nlwPSxtktNu0WSXrFoi5cWqJtXiRRR1JRvN3sb78hKdlyom4E%2BD7EUCTymWdeOcNvRyFdkixSb3hIj06Ojo%2Fh7OwMbgVhCSgOgSC%2Fb%2FAhT2CW%2Ba7Xh5yLKLxnNIfcm%2FvzwXw0H88n0JKKpzBp6%2B2zBGHOpcziVDGeQLBGtBNwISWCB2tGIg3mTXzwYEnEnORkM19nMUlk%2BcEHkrCYRHIueUzzNVHllwEsM5UJWmyYx0QpKuY5U%2Bt5yGTAs0SxZFUuH22BioVkHvEt2BhktlxSgRvmSx5kkoblpwnElKg5%2FuGmVPBFRGOj2JQEayA77ZgEAh82ao3PSxZRQMvtPstjUJo9CUPZAUHR3CyhErgwYIJ20SgkpiiFSXyv1tTa6x8SFU0Cg3EKAY9TLrVe2wW4NwkpIuIrJg2aVCQJScQTCjH6M3Lg69Zd0%2FuvmqreTh9SGijceE%2BijAJfGoSdZx0D9ppKBYtsA5kWozdKWlXsBG7WgsUpfKIRepHCB8H%2Fg7h290%2FT99Pr89vpBSw2sKIJFWhIJ92UYURDpvbM9Ao%2FdiBB