s&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 meat_eater_problem → 10 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbO7tmKJL%2FIdi8HpI2zW1zaLZIUi0VduLRE29xKlI6koni72d%2B%2BQ1Ky5diLCPCHJIxEPvPMK2f0%2FSyiS5LH6m0a0bPJ2fk5XFxcwL0gjINKIRTk9w0uCg6z3He9PhSpiKMHRgsovLk%2FH8yD%2BXjuudCSKs3Ac9saYMYR6FLKPMkUSzmEa8SbgAsZEWm4ZiTWcN7YBw%2BWRMxJQTbzdZ4QLqsXPhDOEhLLuUwTWqyJqt4MYJmrXNDywDwhSlExL5hazyMmwzTnivFVtT3YApUbyTxOt2BjSChRc%2FzBN5lIFzFNttxc4FTNOV0RxR7o3OLMY1xLo%2BGUhGsgOzWZBAIfN2qN6yWLKaARd6%2FlOSitBoki2QFB0fKMUwmpMGCCdtE6JKHIhEl8rtbUGu5fEjXmocF4DWGaZKnUCm434FkeUUTER8xSk4rwiMQpp5Cga2MHvm49N334qqnq4%2FQxo6HCgw8kzimkS4Owc7JjwN5QqWCRbyDXYvRBSeuKTeBuLViSwS80RndS%2BCjS3xDXnv5x%2BmF6e3k%2FvYLFBlaUU4HGdrJNFVE0YmrPTK%2FwZQc4OsmQ0ZZEJIP1iYdUKK1ykgqMoq3FpN1rzUGyLGZUOnC3SZw4XfFUoONa37NBB7Lx4KltsIy3xu4P8Pbda7NzQRWxT3UgkAWLmUIii1SrHel0%2BOx2wPviwDUJVYoyUVcLhRsy7QOuOiBToDowUrFCz00%2FF1eXN7%2Be%2F%2BMLLGicFhjv%2BqzxMH3EdbzB44iNVjVYKDvKQ2V9QXV4conq25i%2FKuMbLg51m0CPdt2RUdGuh09tAA2JJ7uKJRT%2BDSFRRCqRZoit84HnxMSuDlkiulZMGQ6tW5JIujm%2FQwNz%2BNP94Xwj4EHCh1REa5JL%2BNNzBvrha8zjC%2FQYVPnXLv11xQTGAdDlUv9BGTXLZBgyRGzQLBwzIWS47sCb6fXPt1PrXY