imp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   64k lives-eq/$1k · 59% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 41%&lt;br&gt;(Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives + soil_animals&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Grilo&#x27;s soil-animal accounting: ~10^19 soil nematodes, mites and springtails dominate the welfare effects of almost anything. Global-health charities raise food demand and cropland (~137 m^2-yr/$ for GiveWell top charities, ~1.11 kQALY/$ of soil-animal welfare change); with soil lives net-negative, the arithmetic makes GiveWell&#x27;s top charities net-harmful. Only enters once invertebrates already count, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism, where the cropland bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 meat_eater_problem → 10 net_negative_animal_lives → 18 soil_animals" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbO7tmKJL%2B7lwPSxtktLu0WSYrFoi5UWqJtbiVKR1JRvN3sb98hKdly7EUE%2BEMSRSSfeeaVM%2Fp%2BFtElyWP1No3o2fTs%2FBwuLi7gXhDGQaUQCvL7Bh8KDvPcd70%2BFKmIowdGCyi8wA8GwSiYBJ4beGNoSZVm4I3bGmPOEetSyjzJFEs5hGuEnIILGRFpuGYk1ojexAcPlkQEpCCbYJ0nhMtqwQfCWUJiGcg0ocWaqGplAMtc5YKWB4KEKEVFUDC1DiImwzTnivFVtX20BSo3kiBOt2ATSChRAf7gSibSRUyTLTcXOFUBpyui2AMNLE4Q4%2FOWJmouUxaXa9IoPiPhGshOeyaBwMeNWuPzksUU0Ly7ZXkOSmtHokh2QFD0CeMoIBUGTNAuGo0kFAkyie%2FVmlp7%2FkuiIXhoMF5DmCZZKrXe2w14lkcUEfEVs9SkIjwiccopJOj02IGvW5%2FOHr5qqvo4fcxoqPDgA4lzCunSIOzc7xiwN1QqWOQbyLUYfVDSumJTuFsLlmTwC43RyxQ%2BivQ3xLWnf5x9mN1e3s%2BuYLGBFeVUoA%2BcbFPFGo2Y2jPTK1zsAEffGTLakohksD7xkAqlVU5SgcG1tZi0e605SJbFjEoH7jaJE6crngr0Wet7NuhANhk8tQ2W8dbE%2FQHevnttdi6oIvatjg%2ByYDFTSGSRarUjnSif3Q54Xxy4JqFKUSbqaqFwQ6Z9wFUHwwS